‚óè‚Äã one symbol leaks into another‚Äã
‚óè‚Äã eyes become mouths, mouths become blobs, blobs become creatures, creatures
become patterns‚Äã

That is huge.

2. Contour inheritance
A new thing often grows out of the same outline skeleton as the last thing.
Meaning:

‚óè‚Äã the silhouette mutates rather than resets‚Äã
‚óè‚Äã shape edges act like elastic boundaries‚Äã
‚óè‚Äã forms seem to ‚Äúdiscover‚Äù other forms already hidden inside them‚Äã

That ‚Äúfinding other things in the thing‚Äù thing you described ‚Äî yes, that is absolutely visible.

